      <!-- Paragraph-->
      <div>
        <div class="left">
          &#8195;Welcome to Lab 5.
          This lab demonstrates several basic concepts.
          The basic concepts delivered here can be applied in many differing use-cases.
          The code on this webpage asks the user to input the full name of a file (including the file extension)
          and thus returns the file extension of the user's input.<br>
          To achieve this, the user's input is indexed with the last position of a period, and anything coming after the period is accepted as a valid file extension.<br>
          To minimize errors, get_extension.js has several error catching checks built in.<br><br>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <h4>Basic Functionality</h4>
          <p class="margin_small">
            <b>1.</b> The user is proveded with an input box.<br>
            <b>2.</b> User input is thus passed to a variable.<br>
            <b>3.</b> The variable is thus capable of being iterated upon with JavaScript.<br>
          </p>
          <h4>Use-Cases</h4>
          <p class="margin_small">
            <b>1.</b> User input could be used for naming files, events, and any other namable object.<br>
            <b>2.</b> Calculation and iteration is possible using the combination of the input box and JavaScript.<br>
            <b>3.</b> User input could be used to perform search and indexing actions.<br>
          </p>
        </div>
